The majority of men in Kashmir view abortion as a woman’s issue, and are not aware of the legal provisions for abortion. This is one of the findings of a study conducted by the Centre for Social Research (CSR) in collaboration with the Jammu and Kashmir State Legal Services Authority (JKSLSA) and the J&K State AIDS Control Society (JKSACS).

The study, titled ‘Men’s Perceptions and Attitudes towards Abortion in Jammu and Kashmir’, was conducted in 2016 in Srinagar, Baramulla, Anantnag and Pulwama districts. It was based on a sample of 1,000 men, aged 18-45 years, who were interviewed in their homes.
